This is the Batlló House, in Barcelona, of the Catalan architect Antoni Gaudí.
Because of its shape similar to a skeleton, the locals seized it "the house of the bones".
Its organic shapes, its flame color, the innovative use of the stone, the fragments of tiles and mosaics, a facade that reminds the scales and omnipresent gently curved lines, all of which is typical of Antoni Gaudí's secession.
