EU changes rules for obtaining visas
Persons should visit Visa Request Service centres before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and as well as the waiting time.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedure for processing a visa will be changed at the United States Embassy and consulates.
With the new procedure, most applicants must visit Visa Requesting Service Centres (ASCs, for their English stamps) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The ASC staff will receive biometric information from the applicant, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer will be necessary to make a payment for the date, another payment for processing the visa application and more for the mail service to deliver the document.
The vacuum cleaner will only make a single payment covering the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visas on request (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors visas.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Officer, but will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their marks.
Because biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants who will require a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain in this less time than in the past.
Similarly, those applying for visas in Consulates in Juárez, Monterrey and New Laredo will no longer pay the extra fee of $26.
For additional information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/bolettines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
